RE: Does Christian Religion Sure. If she ditched the kids, she might get free. The kids can never be free, until they're big enough to fight back or run away. That's how women get stuck: if they can't carry the kids, they can't run, and they won't leave the kids. On the other hand, the law is a lot more likely to step in when a child is known to be abused than when an adult is known to be abused. (And almost nobody, ever, steps in if the victim of domestic violence is a man. Just saying, to be fair.)
